VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//Codex//Best Kept Secret 2026//EN
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
METHOD:PUBLISH
X-WR-CALNAME:BKS - The Shore
X-WR-TIMEZONE:Europe/Amsterdam
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-01f2f546e1dc5b98@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T140000Z
DTEND:20260612T170000Z
SUMMARY:Fada Jep
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:A leading light in soundsystem movements\n\nSince the early 90s
 \, Fada Jep has been a leading authority in reggae\, dancehall\, dub and a
 ll affiliated musical movements.\nAs a selector\, DJ and label owner\, Jep
  Verhorevoort has sent positive vibrations out at every block party\, club
  and festival you can think of. Fada Jep's passion for his craft is self-e
 vident in his sets and runs as deep as the bass will take him.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-053ae900ea712bfc@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T170000Z
DTEND:20260612T190000Z
SUMMARY:Bibtiana: music from Île Maurice
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Top Notch/Noah's Ark member & DJ goes knee-deep into Mauritian 
 Seggae\n\nMusic isn't just for bread and circuses\; it's a priceless form 
 of resistance. Seggae is a prime example of this.\nSeggae music derives fr
 om Sega\, the traditional folk music from Mauritius. This vibrant strand o
 f dance music was invented in the 80s by Mauritian artist Kaya\; music cre
 ated for the uprising Creole people in Mauritius. Bibtiana will give Segga
 e a vital modern twist with this blistering DJ set.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-e93af5864312c4e8@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T190000Z
DTEND:20260612T210000Z
SUMMARY:DJ Tracksuit
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Dedicated digger of Afro-Caribbean sounds\n\nDJ Tracksuit has w
 orked out the science behind the soiree-making: a true student of the game
  with a nose for vibrant Afro-Caribbean sounds.\nMaking people dance and t
 elling a story behind the decks are indeed one and the same for this Belgi
 an connoisseur and collector. Knowing is half the battle for Timothy Vande
 rputte\; the other half is spinning the dancefloor dizzy with a a cultural
 ly rich\, inclusive experience that engages both body and soul.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-ab6585c3bf8d3eec@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T210000Z
DTEND:20260612T223000Z
SUMMARY:Cami Layé Okún
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Infectious Cuban & Afro-Latin sounds\n\nCuban DJ\, selector\, a
 rtist and radio host Cami Layé Okún conjures up a distinct mix of Cuban 
 disco\, Afro-Caribbean rarities\, and Amazonian funk.\nOther than having a
 n impeccable nose for the best hidden gems\, Cami exemplifies the joy of b
 eing a certified crate digger\; chasing those elusive jams that can unlock
  new windows in body and soul. Cami’s sets are adventurous\, infectious 
 and always tell a bigger story.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a6af35be70aac419@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T223000Z
DTEND:20260613T000000Z
SUMMARY:Susobrino
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Vibrant clash of Latin American jams & electronica\n\nBolivia-b
 orn\, Brussels-based artist Susobrino is deeply connected to Latin America
 ’s rich soundscapes.\nBoth his live sets and DJ sets are driven by rhyth
 m\, emotion\, curiosity and exploration\, blending acoustic instruments an
 d electronics into something grounded\, funny and unpredictable. 'SU SO BR
 I NO' contains boleros\, cumbia\, club music\, folklore\, and film scores 
 all colliding and manifesting into Susobrino’s warped wizardry.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-7cf2a82261b58a27@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T140000Z
DTEND:20260613T170000Z
SUMMARY:Ketama Man
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Certified dealer in dub\, reggae & dancehall\n\nFor over two de
 cades\, Ketama Man has explored Jamaican music from all possible angles\nI
 t didn’t start with (traditional) DJing\, however\, but as an MC in the 
 late 90s. The physicality of those stage shows gave the necessary insight 
 to translate the best reggae\, dub and dancehall to the clubs. That notion
  of physicality also translates to Ketama Man’s insistence to stick to v
 inyl. That's true dedication in both the selecting and igniting the dance 
 floor part of the sum.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-3487240c916255b8@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T170000Z
DTEND:20260613T190000Z
SUMMARY:Rozaly (Archives)
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:A journey through the musical lineages of Curaçao\n\nRozaly is
  a sonic practitioner\, researcher\, curator\, and DJ from Curaçao.\nHe e
 nshrines all the undiscovered micro-styles from her home region\; a musica
 l ode to friends\, and forgotten pillars of Curaçao musical legacy. Expec
 t lots of echo and reverb\, an odyssey of calypso loops\, 80s Bajan crop-o
 vers\, kompa\, chutney\, and much\, much more.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-6e86f3326b73c489@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T190000Z
DTEND:20260613T220000Z
SUMMARY:Aba Shanti-I
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:A peerless reggae/dub apostle of the deepest basses\n\nIf roots
  reggae & dub are still resurgent in Europe and the UK\, you better believ
 e Aba Shanti-I is a big reason why.\nSoundsystem culture hauls the party v
 ibes to any place you can set your mind to and over the past three decades
 \, Aba has forged his own unique frequency in this very lineage: distinct 
 manipulations of reverb and delay into existing reggae classics\, translat
 ing into a peerless sound that’s uniquely his.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f60585017c46a9fb@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T220000Z
DTEND:20260614T000000Z
SUMMARY:Bony Fly
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Adventurous Caribbean and Latinx productions\n\nProducer\, labe
 l owner and DJ\, Bony Fly has been dubbed as Geneva’s king of dancehall 
 and reggaeton.\nBony Fly’s daredevil production style is the big catalys
 t for getting such distinguished titles\; he combines cutting edge digital
  productions with the more classical\, time-honoured craft of analog mixin
 g\, carving out new possibilities within established dance lineages.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-faf765e9763eeb46@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T000000Z
DTEND:20260614T020000Z
SUMMARY:Mia Koden
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Top shelf bass-heavy rhythms\n\nThe lower frequencies are where
  producer/DJ Mia Koden is most at home\, from the womb to the booth.\nKode
 n\, born Sancha Ndeko\, has keen expertise on how low a bass can indeed go
 \, connecting the dots between dub\, dubstep\, grime and other bass-heavy 
 dance transmutations. Ndeko’s sets bring the rapturous energy of soundsy
 stem block parties to each room or stage: odysseys that span generations\,
  bolster communities and honour undersung histories.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-5a46b2631f48db5f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T140000Z
DTEND:20260614T170000Z
SUMMARY:Capiche Collectiv
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:A warm blanket of soulful slow jams\n\nTilburg’s Capiche Coll
 ectiv offer a warm blanket of soul and other types of slow jams\nGroove is
  in the heart\, and Capiche Collectiv’s heart is both receptive and pure
  to the kind of grooves that’ll utilise each muscle\, bone and tendon in
  our bodies. Instead of going harder and faster\, it’s all about being s
 moother\, deeper and more passionate. Preferably with that unmistakable an
 alog glow\, capiche?
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-55f10642b3e0fdbb@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T170000Z
DTEND:20260614T190000Z
SUMMARY:JBN Soundsystem
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Jungle By Night behind the booth\n\nJungle By Night's Tienson\,
  Ko en Pyke are here show off some impressive musical mileage.\nThroughout
  their incessant travels\, these beloved Dutch jazz cats have assembled an
  archive of sounds from all over the world\, a magnitude of music you woul
 dn't believe. Which means time is due to aim those speakers outward\, and 
 unleash those well-cultivated vibes towards Best Kep Secret's fluorescent 
 The Shore area.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-18c1e50b16006f1f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T190000Z
DTEND:20260614T210000Z
SUMMARY:Abiba Sokoto
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Expressive house\, soul and jazz selections\n\nThe warm selecti
 ons of Abiba Sokoto are an ode to the Black music continuum.\nSpanning hou
 se\, electro\, soul and jazz. Abiba showcases her wide-ranging taste throu
 gh her Operator Radio residency\, ALLBLUE\, as well as across numerous rad
 io appearances from RRFM to Future Intel.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d5d0b1a28e4ab07f@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T210000Z
DTEND:20260614T223000Z
SUMMARY:Suze Ijó
LOCATION:The Shore
DESCRIPTION:Vintage house & soul through fresh modern ears\n\nFrom infectio
 us Chicago house to warm\, soulful grooves\; Suze Ijó transports you back
  to the heydays where dance floors were spaces for freedom\, self-expressi
 on and connection.\nIjó's club sets are marked by intentionality and focu
 s\, creating a unique atmosphere for each space and night. To her\, "House
 " is a feeling\, an ambience\, not just a BPM range. Her approach transfor
 ms club nights into collective\, bodily\, and spiritual experiences crafte
 d by everyone involved.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
